<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        AutoSave Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Legacy Event Point retained for documentation only. AutoSave is not used by the current release gameplay.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What AutoSave Was Intended To Do
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>AutoSave</Bold> Event Point appears to be a legacy mission feature from earlier
        development. At one point, automatic mission saving was planned. The Event Point likely
        existed so a mission could trigger an autosave when the player reached a certain point,
        completed a section, or passed some internal checkpoint.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This system was scrapped. In the current release workflow, AutoSave is not used for normal
        missions and should not be relied on for mission progression, checkpoints, recovery, or
        gameplay scripting.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_autosave_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Do not use for new missions:</Run>
                <Run>
                    AutoSave is not in active use anymore. It is a leftover development feature and should be treated as legacy/scrapped.
                    Use normal mission objectives, triggers, messages, timers, and win/lose Event Points instead.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Why It Still Appears
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        AutoSave may still appear in the Event Point type list because the editor and file format
        expose older Event Point definitions. Not every Event Point in the list is useful in the
        final release version of the game.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Some Event Points are active and important. Others are unused, partially implemented,
        development-only, or retained for compatibility with old mission data. AutoSave belongs in
        the legacy/unused category.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Behaviour in Current Missions
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        For current mission authoring, treat AutoSave as having no useful gameplay effect. Do not
        build mission logic that depends on it. If you need the player to recover progress or advance
        through a staged mission sequence, use proper mission logic instead.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Objectives</Bold> and <Bold>Sub Objectives</Bold> to track mission progress.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Dependency</Bold> triggers to sequence mission events.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Messages</Bold>, <Bold>Conversations</Bold>, or <Bold>Nav Beacons</Bold> to guide the player.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Timers</Bold> and <Bold>Counters</Bold> for staged logic.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>End Game Win</Bold> or <Bold>End Game Lose</Bold> for mission completion or failure.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Recommended Documentation Note
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        If you encounter AutoSave in an old mission file, document it as a legacy Event Point and
        verify whether the mission still behaves correctly without relying on it. If creating a new
        mission, avoid adding AutoSave unless you are deliberately testing historical or unused
        functionality.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Summary:</Run>
                <Run>
                    AutoSave was planned during development, but the feature was scrapped.
                    It remains useful to document, but it is not useful for normal playable mission creation.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>
